Patient: What kind of exercise is good for me, considering my heart condition?
Healthcare Educator: Walking is a good start. It's gentle and can be easily adjusted to your comfort.

Patient: How long should I walk each day?
Healthcare Educator: Start with 5-10 minutes a day. Gradually aim for 30 minutes most days of the week.

Patient: Are there any exercises I should avoid?
Healthcare Educator: Avoid high-intensity workouts. They may strain your heart. Stick to low-impact exercises.

Patient: Can I do household chores as a form of exercise?
Healthcare Educator: Yes, chores can be good exercise. Just remember to pace yourself and not to overdo it.

Patient: Is it safe for me to exercise alone?
Healthcare Educator: Ideally, have someone with you. But if you're alone, have a phone nearby in case you need help.